Session 12 & 13 is a classic CDAC favorite because it blends architecture + IDS internals + DoS/DDoS + labs (Snort, OSSEC, Wireshark, iptables, LOIC). Expect scenario-based MCQs here.

Below are 30 CCEE-grade MCQs (10 Basic + 10 Intermediate + 10 Advanced) strictly aligned with Session 12 & 13 + Lab 17 & 18, designed for 90%+ scoring.

Network Defense & Countermeasures ‚Äì Session 12 & 13
BASIC MCQs (1‚Äì10)
1. A sudden spike in network traffic is a common symptom of:
A. Phishing
B. DoS attack
C. Malware infection
D. Insider attack

2. IDS sensors are mainly responsible for:
A. Blocking traffic
B. Collecting and analyzing data
C. Encrypting packets
D. Load balancing

3. Network-based IDS sensors monitor:
A. System logs
B. File integrity
C. Network traffic
D. User activity

4. Host-based IDS sensors monitor:
A. Switch traffic
B. Router logs
C. System events and logs
D. Firewall rules

5. A three-tier architecture typically consists of:
A. Client, Server, Database
B. Presentation, Application, Database
C. Network, Host, Application
D. User, IDS, Firewall

6. Denial of Service attacks mainly affect:
A. Confidentiality
B. Integrity
C. Availability
D. Authentication

7. DDoS differs from DoS because it uses:
A. One attacker
B. Multiple distributed sources
C. Encryption
D. VPN

8. IDS agents primarily run on:
A. Network devices
B. End hosts
C. Routers only
D. Firewalls only

9. LOIC is mainly used to:
A. Scan vulnerabilities
B. Capture packets
C. Simulate DoS attacks
D. Block traffic

10. Rate limiting helps mitigate DoS by:
A. Blocking all traffic
B. Limiting request rate
C. Encrypting packets
D. Logging attacks

INTERMEDIATE MCQs (11‚Äì20)
11. Which symptom BEST indicates a DDoS attack?
A. Slow database query
B. Multiple IPs flooding a service
C. Corrupted files
D. Login failures

12. Tiered architecture improves security by:
A. Reducing bandwidth
B. Isolating components
C. Increasing latency
D. Removing firewalls

13. IDS sensor placement should ensure:
A. Minimal visibility
B. Maximum traffic visibility
C. Encryption only
D. Low bandwidth

14. Host-based sensors are BEST for detecting:
A. Network scans
B. File integrity changes
C. DDoS attacks
D. Packet floods

15. Agents in IDS architecture communicate with:
A. Firewall
B. IDS Manager
C. Router
D. Switch

16. The IDS Manager is responsible for:
A. Packet capture
B. Centralized analysis and correlation
C. Blocking traffic
D. Load balancing

17. Which iptables feature is useful for DoS mitigation?
A. NAT
B. Rate limiting
C. Logging only
D. VLAN tagging

18. Blacklisting mitigates DoS by:
A. Allowing traffic
B. Blocking known malicious IPs
C. Encrypting data
D. Load balancing

19. Wireshark helps identify DoS symptoms by showing:
A. File changes
B. Abnormal traffic patterns
C. System logs
D. Firewall rules

20. Snort is typically deployed as a:
A. Host-based sensor
B. Network-based sensor
C. Firewall
D. VPN

