21. In a three-tier architecture, the MOST secure placement of database is:
A. DMZ
B. Internal network
C. Public network
D. Internet-facing

22. Excessive SYN packets without ACK indicate:
A. UDP flood
B. SYN flood attack
C. ICMP flood
D. DNS amplification

23. DDoS mitigation is difficult mainly due to:
A. Encryption
B. Distributed attack sources
C. Weak IDS
D. Firewall rules

24. Sensor failure impacts IDS by causing:
A. False positives
B. Blind spots
C. Encryption failure
D. High latency

25. Agents performing file integrity monitoring detect:
A. Network floods
B. Unauthorized file changes
C. Bandwidth usage
D. Port scans

26. IDS agents must be lightweight to:
A. Increase detection
B. Reduce host performance impact
C. Block traffic
D. Encrypt data

27. A centralized IDS Manager helps in:
A. Single point of failure
B. Event correlation and reporting
C. Packet forwarding
D. NAT

28. LOIC attack traffic is BEST mitigated using:
A. Signature-based IDS only
B. Rate limiting and IP filtering
C. Antivirus
D. Encryption

29. Deploying both network and host sensors improves:
A. Bandwidth
B. Detection coverage
C. Latency
D. Encryption

30. From CCEE perspective, effective DoS defense requires:
A. Single firewall
B. Layered mitigation techniques
C. IDS only
D. VPN

